---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Zero-Budget Strategy" section="zero-budget">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">Channels · Budget = $0</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">What you can ship <em>before Jim approves a dollar.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Most of marketing's first-90-day impact doesn't require paid budget. Founder-led content, customer marketing-as-acquisition, earned media, partnership co-marketing, podcast guest pitching. Here's the playbook with no media spend, organized so you can execute Day 1.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="zero-budget"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Progress: <span data-progress-here="zero-budget">0 / 0</span></p>

  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <div class="lbl">The reframe</div>
    <p>AI tooling ($400-900/mo) is <strong>infrastructure</strong>, not marketing spend. It comes from product/eng or G&A. The plays below assume ZERO marketing media budget — pure organic, owned, earned, and partnership. Everything here is shippable in your first 60 days while Jim is approving the bigger paid budget.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- THE 5 LEVERS -->
  <h2>Five zero-budget levers</h2>
  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-zest">01</span><h4>Founder visibility</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Jim + you + customers + partners producing 5-10 LinkedIn posts/week with thought leadership angles. Compounds. Zero spend.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-zest">02</span><h4>Customer marketing as acquisition</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">5,000 practices are your warmest, lowest-cost channel. Referrals, case studies, co-branded content, advocacy programs.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-zest">03</span><h4>Earned media pitching</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Becker's, Group Dentistry Now, Dental Economics, DrBicuspid all hungry for content. Pitch quarterly. Costs nothing but research time.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-zest">04</span><h4>Partnership co-marketing</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Sunbit, Dental Intelligence, Hint Health, NexHealth all benefit from joint webinars + case studies. Mutual amplification, no spend.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-zest">05</span><h4>Podcast guest tour</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">12+ dental podcasts hungry for guests. Jim + customers as guests = 6-9 months of always-on brand presence at $0.</p></div>
  </div>

  <!-- LEVER 1: FOUNDER VISIBILITY -->
  <h2>Lever 01 · Founder visibility <em>(Jim + you)</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>The model</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Jordon Comstock (BoomCloud) and Megan Lohman (Plan Forward) win at this. They're on every podcast, posting weekly, hosting newsletters. <strong>Jim has more credibility, a bigger company, more data, and a better story — he just isn't using it yet.</strong> This is the single biggest zero-budget lever.</p>

    <h4>Jim's LinkedIn content cadence — proposed</h4>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h4>Posting cadence</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.875rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>2-3 LinkedIn posts/week from the CEO's profile</li>
          <li>1 long-form article/month (LinkedIn newsletter)</li>
          <li>1 quarterly thought piece (cross-published Clerri blog + LinkedIn)</li>
          <li>You ghostwrite, Jim approves + adds personal voice, you post</li>
          <li>Time cost: 90 min/week for you, 15 min/week for Jim</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Content pillars (rotation)</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.875rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li><strong>Industry observation:</strong> "30% of dentists dropped networks last year. Here's what they did next."</li>
          <li><strong>Customer story:</strong> "[Practice] grew revenue 40% switching from PPO-dependence to membership."</li>
          <li><strong>Strategic POV:</strong> "Why membership infrastructure is the only owned channel left in dentistry."</li>
          <li><strong>Behind-the-scenes:</strong> "What we learned merging Kleer + Membersy into Clerri."</li>
          <li><strong>Counter-narrative:</strong> "Why I disagree with the 'AI replaces marketing teams' take."</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h4>Tasks</h4>
    <div data-section="zero-budget">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-jim-01-pitch" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Pitch the CEO on personal LinkedIn cadence — 2-3 posts/week, you ghostwrite</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-jim-02-pillars" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Establish 5 content pillars + 30-post backlog (90 days of content)</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-jim-03-newsletter" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Launch Jim's LinkedIn newsletter — quarterly cadence, "Membership Infrastructure"</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-jim-04-john-jacob" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Extend cadence to John (CS) + Jacob (product) — 1 post/week each, different angles</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-jim-05-employee-advocacy" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Employee advocacy — get 10-15 Clerri employees re-sharing on LinkedIn with personal commentary</div></div></label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- LEVER 2: CUSTOMER MARKETING -->
  <h2>Lever 02 · Customer marketing <em>as acquisition</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>The insight</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">5,000 practices is the warmest channel in dental. Every existing customer knows 3-10 other practice owners. Most B2B SaaS treats customer marketing as a retention thing. <strong>For Clerri it's the cheapest acquisition channel.</strong></p>

    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h4>Plays to ship Day 1</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.875rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li><strong>Referral program:</strong> Practice refers practice → both get 3 months free OR a $1,000 marketing credit</li>
          <li><strong>Case study production engine</strong> (Workflow D): turn every successful customer into 3 content assets (article, LinkedIn post, conference talk)</li>
          <li><strong>"Membership Champions" certification:</strong> Free CE for office managers who complete a Clerri training program. Builds advocates + product expertise.</li>
          <li><strong>Customer Slack community:</strong> Practices share what's working. Peer-to-peer = lower CS load + organic advocacy.</li>
          <li><strong>Quarterly customer summit (virtual):</strong> 90-min event, customers share growth tactics. Recorded + chopped into 50+ content pieces.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Plays to ship within 90 days</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.875rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li><strong>Advocate ambassador program:</strong> Top 50 customers get invited to be public advocates. They get a "Clerri Champion" badge, early product access, conference comps.</li>
          <li><strong>Customer-led webinar series:</strong> One customer/month does a webinar. Clerri promotes + repurposes.</li>
          <li><strong>Co-branded marketing assets</strong> (Workflow C): customers get done-for-them marketing materials for THEIR patient enrollment. Sticky + advocacy-generating.</li>
          <li><strong>Annual "State of Dental Membership" report</strong>: anonymized customer data → category-defining content asset.</li>
          <li><strong>Customer Advisory Board:</strong> 12 hand-picked practices. Quarterly virtual meetings. Voice into roadmap + future case studies.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h4>Tasks</h4>
    <div data-section="zero-budget">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-cust-01-referral" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Design + launch referral program with CS + Finance approval</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-cust-02-champions" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">"Membership Champions" CE certification — design with Clerri University team</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-cust-03-slack" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Customer Slack community — pilot with top 50 most engaged practices</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-cust-04-cab" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Customer Advisory Board — recruit 12 practices, first meeting by Day 90</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-cust-05-summit" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Quarterly virtual customer summit — first edition planned for Day 75-90</div></div></label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- LEVER 3: EARNED MEDIA -->
  <h2>Lever 03 · Earned media <em>pitching playbook</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>Top publications + editors</h4>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto">
      <table class="data-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Publication</th><th>What they want</th><th>Pitch angle</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Becker's Dental + DSO Review</strong></td><td>DSO leadership content, executive interviews, M&A coverage</td><td>"Inside the Kleer+Membersy merger to Clerri" exec interview · Charlesbank thesis on dental consolidation · Quarterly DSO trends piece</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Group Dentistry Now</strong></td><td>Practical operator content, podcast guests, sponsored features</td><td>Jim on the Group Dentistry Now Show · "How 7 of top 10 DSOs scaled membership" guide · Featured Company spot</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Dental Economics</strong> (Endeavor)</td><td>Practice owner business content, ROI math</td><td>"The $3-6M PPO write-off you're not calculating" cover story · ROI calculator embed · Practice owner case study</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>DrBicuspid</strong></td><td>News, product launches, M&A</td><td>Press release distribution · Stream Dental / Subscribili counter-narrative · ADSO Summit coverage</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Decisions in Dentistry</strong></td><td>Clinical-business intersection, CE content</td><td>"Why membership plans reduce treatment plan friction" · Co-published with clinical expert</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Dental Products Report</strong></td><td>Tech + product reviews</td><td>"What dental practices are spending on tech in 2026" data piece using Clerri's customer base</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h4>The pitching cadence</h4>
    <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
      <li><strong>Monthly:</strong> 1 newsworthy pitch (product launch, customer milestone, data release)</li>
      <li><strong>Quarterly:</strong> 1 thought leadership piece pitched to 3-5 publications</li>
      <li><strong>Annually:</strong> "State of Dental Membership" report — exclusive embargo to one outlet, then wide release</li>
      <li><strong>Response time:</strong> Editor replies = respond within 24 hours, even just "got it, drafting." Speed = win.</li>
    </ul>

    <div data-section="zero-budget">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-pr-01-editor-list" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Build editor list with email + LinkedIn for 6 top publications</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-pr-02-pitch-templates" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Draft 3 pitch templates: news, thought leadership, exclusive data</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-pr-03-merger-story" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Pitch "Inside the Kleer+Membersy merger" exec interview to Becker's by Day 30</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-pr-04-newsroom" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Set up newsroom on clerri.com — single source for press releases + media kit</div></div></label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- LEVER 4: PARTNERSHIPS -->
  <h2>Lever 04 · Partnership co-marketing</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>The formula</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">Partner brings their audience, you bring yours, both amplify. Costs nothing but coordination. <strong>The trick: pick partners with audience YOU don't reach yet.</strong></p>

    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Tier 1 · Strategic</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.85rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Sunbit (financing) — joint webinar on "$4-5K procedure conversion"</li>
          <li>Dental Intelligence — co-published "Membership ROI" study using their analytics data</li>
          <li>Hint Health (DPC) — "Membership across healthcare" thought piece</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Tier 2 · Channel</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.85rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>NexHealth — patient scheduling + membership integration story</li>
          <li>Pearl AI — "AI-powered practice" co-content (positioning halo)</li>
          <li>RevenueWell — patient communication + membership lifecycle joint webinar</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Tier 3 · Community</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.85rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>DEO — annual sponsorship + speaking slot at Operations Intensive</li>
          <li>Nifty Thrifty (Glenn Vo) — Deal of the Month + podcast guest</li>
          <li>AADOM — Featured Company placement</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h4>Co-marketing motion templates</h4>
    <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
      <li><strong>Joint webinar (60 min):</strong> 30 min content + 30 min Q&A. Both audiences invited. Lead capture split 50/50. ~$0 cost.</li>
      <li><strong>Co-authored report:</strong> Both contribute data, both promote, both get logo on cover. 5-10 page PDF.</li>
      <li><strong>Embedded case study:</strong> Featured in each other's customer stories with mutual link backs.</li>
      <li><strong>Joint podcast episode:</strong> Two CEOs interview each other on a respected industry podcast.</li>
      <li><strong>Cross-promoted newsletter feature:</strong> 1 month each, feature each other in your respective newsletters.</li>
    </ul>

    <div data-section="zero-budget">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-part-01-sunbit" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Sunbit joint webinar — "Converting $4-5K procedures with financing + membership"</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-part-02-di" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Dental Intelligence co-published ROI study using their analytics</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-part-03-hint" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Hint Health (DPC) "Membership Infrastructure" thought piece — sets horizontal expansion narrative</div></div></label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- LEVER 5: PODCAST GUEST TOUR -->
  <h2>Lever 05 · Podcast guest tour</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>The play</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem">BoomCloud's Comstock and Plan Forward's Lohman dominate dental podcasts. Clerri has bigger story, bigger company, bigger data — but no founder presence. Fix this in 90 days.</p>

    <h4>Target podcasts — pitch Jim + customers as guests</h4>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto">
      <table class="data-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Podcast</th><th>Host</th><th>Audience</th><th>Pitch</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Group Dentistry Now Show</td><td>Bill Neumann / Kim Larson</td><td>DSO C-suite</td><td>Jim on "Inside the largest DSO membership platform"</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Bulletproof Dental Practice</td><td>Boulden / Spodak</td><td>Owner-dentists</td><td>Jim + customer practice on PPO escape story</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Nifty Thrifty (Glenn Vo)</td><td>Glenn Vo</td><td>Solo + small group dentists</td><td>"Uncomplicating Dentistry" + Deal of the Month promo</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Dental A Team</td><td>Kiera Dent</td><td>Consultants + multi-doc</td><td>Membership as a practice transformation lever</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Dentistry Uncensored (Dentaltown)</td><td>Howard Farran</td><td>Broad dentist</td><td>Jim on the merger story + category future</td></tr>
          <tr><td>T-Bone Speaks Dentistry</td><td>Tarun Agarwal</td><td>GP audience</td><td>Practice-level membership ROI deep dive</td></tr>
          <tr><td>AADOM Radio</td><td>AADOM</td><td>Practice managers</td><td>Featured Company placement</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Dentistry's Growing Edge</td><td>Pierce / Patterson</td><td>Newer dentists</td><td>"How young dentists should think about membership early"</td></tr>
          <tr><td>The Productive Dentist</td><td>Bruce Baird</td><td>Practice owners</td><td>Productivity + membership intersection</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Raving Patients (Pankey Institute)</td><td>Bryn Cooper</td><td>Patient experience</td><td>Member experience as patient retention play</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h4>Cost</h4>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem"><strong>Guest spots = $0.</strong> Sponsorship spots = $1-3K/episode (covered in Ad Spend Tiers). Goal: 10+ guest spots in first 90 days, building to 25+ in year 1.</p>

    <div data-section="zero-budget">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-pod-01-pitch-list" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Build pitch list with host emails + LinkedIn for top 10 podcasts</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-pod-02-gdn" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Book Jim on Group Dentistry Now Show by Day 60</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-pod-03-bulletproof" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Book Jim + customer on Bulletproof Dental Practice by Day 90</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="zb-pod-04-glenn" data-section="zero-budget" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Glenn Vo / Nifty Thrifty — Deal of the Month + podcast appearance</div></div></label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 90-DAY ROADMAP -->
  <h2>90-day zero-budget roadmap</h2>
  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Days 1-30</span>
      <h4>Foundation</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.85rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>CEO content cadence pitched + first 5 posts shipped</li>
        <li>Newsroom on clerri.com live</li>
        <li>Press contact list built</li>
        <li>3 podcast pitches sent</li>
        <li>Sunbit joint webinar scoped</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Days 31-60</span>
      <h4>Engine running</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.85rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>CEO LinkedIn cadence at 2-3 posts/week</li>
        <li>Becker's exec interview pitched</li>
        <li>First Sunbit joint webinar live</li>
        <li>2 podcast guest spots completed</li>
        <li>Referral program live</li>
        <li>Customer Advisory Board recruiting</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="pill pill-zest">Days 61-90</span>
      <h4>Compounding</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.85rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>5+ podcast guest spots completed</li>
        <li>Customer Slack community piloted</li>
        <li>Q1 thought leadership piece published in 2+ outlets</li>
        <li>First customer-led webinar live</li>
        <li>CAB first meeting held</li>
        <li>3 partner co-marketing engagements active</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <div class="lbl">The numbers it should drive</div>
    <p>Zero-budget plays should generate measurable signals within 90 days:</p>
    <ul style="font-size:0.95rem;padding-left:1.25rem;margin:0.5rem 0">
      <li>CEO LinkedIn followers: +500-2,000 (start whatever baseline)</li>
      <li>Branded search volume: +30-50% on "Clerri" queries</li>
      <li>Inbound demo requests citing podcast/article: 5-15 in Day 60-90 window</li>
      <li>Referral program leads: 10-30 in 90 days (depending on existing customer engagement)</li>
      <li>Earned media placements: 3-5 in 90 days</li>
      <li>Partner co-marketing leads: 50-200 (split with partner)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">Zero-budget execution notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="zero-budget-notes" placeholder="What's working, what stalled, where the CEO is engaging, partnership responses..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/ad-spend"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">Ad Spend Tiers</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri/ad-strategy"><span class="dir">Next →</span><span class="name">Ad Creative & Targeting</span></a>
  </div>

</div>
</ClerriLayout>
